Cal Grant wrote:
>I'm
> wondering if the sound could be internal engine stuff, and
mostly I'm
> wondering if one could hear anything like this sound from
outside, if it
> were coming from inside.

If you want to isolate the source of odd sounds in/around
your engine, use a large screwdriver as a stethoscope -- 
place the tip of the screwdriver to the part you suspect of
making the noise, and the handle to your ear.

It may look silly, but it works!

